ead-only review state"},{"id":"d","text":"The cycle is paused and waiting for manager approval before it can be activated"}],"explanation":"Planning is the status every new cycle starts in, and it's fully workable: add, remove, reorder, and complete jobs, and complete or roll the cycle over from here. It's not a draft waiting on a switch — plan and run the cycle right in Planning. Marking a cycle Active adds only the days-remaining countdown."},{"id":"pl4","text":"You complete a cycle and choose 'Complete & Roll Over'. What happens to the three incomplete jobs?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"They are permanently removed and must be re-created from scratch"},{"id":"b","text":"They stay in the completed cycle and are marked as failed"},{"id":"c","text":"They are automatically copied to a new cycle that starts the day after the old one ends, flagged with a rolled-over badge","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"They return to the backlog and lose all planning context"}],"explanation":"Complete & Roll Over starts a new cycle the day after the finished one ends, keeping the same length. Every unfinished job is carried into the new cycle and marked as rolled over, shown with a small replay icon."},{"id":"pl5","text":"How does the backlog panel on the left know which jobs to show?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It shows all jobs in the system regardless of status or cycle"},{"id":"b","text":"It shows all backlog jobs that are NOT already committed to the currently selected cycle, filtered by search and priority","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It only shows jobs assigned to the logged-in user"},{"id":"d","text":"It shows jobs from the Kanban board's first column only"}],"explanation":"The backlog panel shows all jobs from the backlog minus any that are already committed to the selected cycle. It also respects the search (by job number or title) and priority filters. When you commit a job, it instantly disappears from the backlog list."},{"id":"pl6","text":"You want to change the order of committed jobs in the cycle board. How do you do this?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Click column headers to sort alphabetically or by priority"},{"id":"b","text":"Drag jobs by the handle on the left side of each one to reorder them","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Open the cycle edit window and use an 'Order' menu for each job"},{"id":"d","text":"You cannot reorder entries — they are always sorted by the date they were committed"}],"explanation":"Each job on the cycle board has a drag handle on its left side. Drag jobs up or down to change their order. Your new order is saved automatically."},{"id":"pl7","text":"What information does the cycle board header display when a cycle is Active?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Only the cycle name and status"},{"id":"b","text":"Cycle name, date range (start – end), days-remaining countdown, done count (X / Y), and a status label","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"A Gantt chart showing each job's timeline within the cycle"},{"id":"d","text":"The cycle name and a list of team members assigned to the cycle"}],"explanation":"The header of an Active cycle shows the cycle name, date range, days remaining (counting down to the end date), done count (for example, '5 / 12'), and a colored status label (blue for Active). A progress bar below it shows how much is done."},{"id":"pl8","text":"You click 'Complete' (without rollover) on an active cycle that has 4 incomplete jobs. What happens to those jobs?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"They are deleted from the system"},{"id":"b","text":"They remain in the completed cycle marked as incomplete, and return to the backlog for future planning","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"They are automatically moved to the next active cycle"},{"id":"d","text":"They are archived and cannot be accessed again"}],"explanation":"Completing a cycle without rollover marks the cycle as Completed. The incomplete entries stay on the cycle record as historical data, and the jobs themselves return to the backlog where they can be committed to a future cycle."},{"id":"pl9","text":"What fields are required when creating a new planning cycle?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Name, Start Date, End Date, and Goals are all required"},{"id":"b","text":"Name, Start Date, and End Date are required. Goals is optional.","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Only the Name is required — dates are auto-calculated from the team calendar"},{"id":"d","text":"Start Date and End Date are required. Name is auto-generated from the date range."}],"explanation":"Creating a cycle needs a Name, a Start Date, and an End Date. Goals is optional. The End Date must fall after the Start Date. The cycle's length is worked out for you from the two dates."},{"id":"pl10","text":"A committed entry in the cycle board shows a replay icon badge. What does this indicate?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The job has been restarted after being previously completed"},{"id":"b","text":"The entry was automatically rolled over from a previous cycle's incomplete work","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The job is on hold and waiting for materials"},{"id":"d","text":"The entry has been edited since it was originally committed"}],"explanation":"The replay icon means the job was rolled over from an earlier cycle. When you use 'Complete & Roll Over', unfinished jobs from the finished cycle carry into the new one, each marked as rolled over."},{"id":"pl11","text":"You want to remove a job from the current cycle without completing it. What happens?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The job is immediately removed with no confirmation"},{"id":"b","text":"A confirmation window appears. On confirm, the job is taken off the cycle and comes back in the backlog.","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The job is archived and removed from both the cycle and the backlog"},{"id":"d","text":"You cannot remove jobs from a cycle — you can only mark them complete or wait for the cycle to end"}],"explanation":"Clicking the X on a job opens a confirmation window asking you to confirm. Once you confirm, the job is taken off the cycle and comes back in the backlog on the left."},{"id":"pl12","text":"The progress bar on the cycle board shows '75%' and the count shows '6 / 8'. What does this tell you?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"75% of the cycle's time has elapsed and 6 out of 8 team members are assigned"},{"id":"b","text":"6 out of 8 committed entries have been marked complete, which is 75% of the total","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"6 jobs are in progress and 8 are in the backlog, with 75% of the backlog committed"},{"id":"d","text":"The cycle budget is 75% spent with 6 of 8 purchase orders fulfilled"}],"explanation":"The completion count 'X / Y' shows completed entries vs. total committed entries. The progress bar fills to the corresponding percentage. In this case, 6 of 8 entries are marked complete (6/8 = 75%)."},{"id":"pl13","text":"A Production Worker (or Engineer/PM) opens the planning page and tries to commit a backlog job to the current cycle. What happens?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It works the same as for a manager — any role that can see a cycle can also change it"},{"id":"b","text":"The action is turned away — adding, removing, reordering, completing jobs, and creating, activating, or completing cycles all take a Manager or Admin","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The job is committed but flagged for manager approval before it counts"},{"id":"d","text":"The planning page never loads for non-managers, so the question can't arise"}],"explanation":"Viewing a cycle is open to Admins, Managers, PMs, Engineers, and Production Workers, but EVERY change — create, edit, activate, complete or roll over, add a job, remove a job, reorder jobs, and mark a job done — is limited to Managers and Admins. Anyone else who tries a change is turned away. Planning is a manager-run activity the whole team can watch."},{"id":"pl14","text":"You just created a cycle and it's sitting in Planning 